<TEXT>
 a u.s. businessman accused of spying says he has no chance of getting a fair
 trial in russia.
 edmond pope appeared in a moscow courtroom today and read from a 40-page
 statement, denying charges of espionage, and protesting his treatment by the
 court.
 russian prosecutors say pope tried to buy secret blueprints for a high-speed
 torpedo used by the russian military.
 pope's supporters say he was seeking information on an old russian underwater
 propulsion system.
